type(scope?): subject

<commit body>

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Example:
# feat(server): Implement generating secret key
#
# Now, client is generating a new secret key for the handshake (see issue #21).
# This is needed because the communication between server and client will be 
# encrypted with a secret key that is randomly created for every new session. 
#
# --------------------
# Tag can be 
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (refactoring code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    chore    (nomen est omen)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    version  (version bump/new release; no production code change)
#    perf     (improving performance)
#    revert   (revert changes)
#    ci       (changes to continuous integration)
#
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#   * Use the imperative mood in the subject line
#   * Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#   * Can use multiple lines with "-" or "*" for bullet points in body
# --------------------